                <head>330. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Foreign Ministers did not meet on Saturday May 23 or Sunday May 24. However,
                    at 10:30 a.m. on May 24 Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_HCA1"
                        >Herter</persName> discussed at length with <persName corresp="#p_CDMM1"
                        >Couve de Murville</persName> questions affecting U.S.-French relations. A
                    memorandum of their conversation is printed in <ref target="frus1958-60v07p2"
                        >volume VII, Part 2, Document 116</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
